    <fr:title text="Impaired">Impaired</fr:title>
    <fr:authors />
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Impaired attacks roll d4 only and cannot gain bonus dice or benefit from <fr:link type="local" href="feats.xml" addr="feats" title="Feats">Feats</fr:link>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:title text="Backlinks">Backlinks</fr:title>
        <fr:authors />
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>280</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">gambits</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>gambits.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Gambits">Gambits</fr:title>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Attacker may discard an number of Attack dice of 4 or higher to perform Gambits, each causing one of the effects below. The affected foe must be a target of the original attack.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>For Gambits other than Bolster and Move the target receives a <fr:link type="local" href="virtues.xml" addr="virtues" title="Virtues"><fr:strong>VIG</fr:strong></fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="saves.xml" addr="saves" title="Saves">SAVE</fr:link> to ignore the effects.

  <fr:ul><fr:li>Bolster the Attack for +1 total Damage</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Move after the Attack, even if you already moved or are unable to move</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Repel a foe away from you</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Stop a foe from moving next turn</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:link type="local" href="impaired.xml" addr="impaired" title="Impaired">Impair</fr:link> a weapon on their next turn</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Trap a shield until you next turn</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Dismount a foe</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Secret 8th thing with similar level of impact</fr:li></fr:ul>

  If a die of 8 or higher is used in melee then a Strong Gambit is performed and the attacker chooses one of the following:

  <fr:ul><fr:li>No <fr:link type="local" href="saves.xml" addr="saves" title="Saves">Save</fr:link> is granted to the target</fr:li>
    <fr:li>Greater effect such as disarming an item, breaking a wooden shield or weapon, or removing a helm. This does not increase the Damage from Bolster.</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>281</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">virtues</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>virtues.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Virtues">Virtues</fr:title>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>There are three virtues for knights: <fr:strong>VIG</fr:strong>OUR, <fr:strong>CLA</fr:strong>RITY, <fr:strong>SPI</fr:strong>RIT.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>They roll d12 + d6 for each of them and keep the results.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>Vig</fr:strong>our is restored by consuming Sustenance or spending a full day in warm hospitality.</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:strong>Cla</fr:strong>rity is restored by consuming Stimulant or receiving guidance from a Seer.</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:strong>Spi</fr:strong>rit is restored by consuming Sacrament or indulging a Passion.</fr:li></fr:ul>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>At <fr:strong>VIG</fr:strong> 0 you are Exhausted and cannot Attack if you have moved this turn.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>At <fr:strong>CLA</fr:strong> 0 you are <fr:link type="local" href="exposed.xml" addr="exposed" title="Exposed">Exposed</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>At <fr:strong>SPI</fr:strong> 0 your attacks are <fr:link type="local" href="impaired.xml" addr="impaired" title="Impaired">Impaired</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
